# 4. 俺はもう二度と

Akito: You're having trouble achieving that same energy...?
Toya: Yes.
Toya: Through trial and error, I tried to find the best way to work in our feelings while trying to achieve that energy. But nothing has worked so far...
An: Hmm... I think it's a really good song...
Toya: You do? Thank you...
Toya: Still, I feel like it's missing quite a lot.
Toya: I want this song to be an expression of our resolve, so it needs to feel powerful...
An: Then, what if you built things up more before the chorus by adding another part or something.
Toya: I see. That could work...
Akito: Raising the tempo during the first verse could also help give the beginning of the song more momentum.
KAITO: ...
KAITO: Your song has gotten better each time, so the listener should be able to understand what you're trying to achieve...
KAITO: But you may be right about it not having the same energy as what you heard during RAD WEEKEND.
Toya: You think so too, KAITO...?
Toya: Which means... It may be necessary to further analyze the songs that were played during RAD WEEKEND...
Toya: If I can break them down and learn why Ken and his team's songs are so compelling, then I might be able to find the key to making my song better.
KAITO: Then, I'll help you with that!
Toya: Huh? You will...? I really appreciate it.
Toya: (Starting over and going with a different sort of sound didn't help either...)
Toya: (I've tried everything I could think of... But...)
Akito: Hey, Toya, you there?
Toya: Oh, sorry... What were you just saying?
Akito: Nothing. We were just shooting the breeze, but you didn't seem very engaged in our conversation.
Toya: Oh, okay... I apologize for not paying attention.
Akito: That's fine. We all have a lot on our plate right now.
Akito: I mean, I'm also pretty stuck... I don't know what I'm supposed to do next.
Toya: I see...
Akito: But we've gotta find a way to succeed...
Akito: We have to keep moving forward. Am I right...?
Toya: Yes... You're absolutely right.
Toya: ...
Toya: (I've tried looking at why my song isn't able to achieve that energy from multiple different angles...)
Toya: (I've changed the tempo and adjusted the notes many times. I've tried using different sound sources because I thought it was a quality issue. I even began learning about how non-classical music is composed.)
Toya: (Wait.. Was I too hasty trying to apply that knowledge...? But KAITO didn't think I was doing anything wrong technically...)
Toya: (I'm responsible for expressing how we all feel...)
Toya: (But I'm failing to do so. Why is that?)
Toya: (I feel like I'm wandering around in the dark while grasping at straws...)
Toya: (At this rate...)
Toya: (I'm going to fail them...)
Toya: (I'm going to fail at my task of writing this team's songs.)
Toya: (If that were to happen...)
Junior High School Toya: I can't...
Junior High School Toya: I can't do it...!
Junior High School Toya: I can't live up to you and everyone's expectations, Dad...!
Toya: ...
Toya: No, I can't let that happen...
Toya: I'm done running...!
Toya: I'm not going to let them down! I'm going to succeed...!
Toya: (I still don't know what I'm doing wrong, but I just have to keep trying.)
Toya: (Anything I can think of...! Anything that I haven't tried yet...!!)
Toya's Father: Can I get a refill...?
Toya's Mother: For your coffee? Sure. Just give me one second.
Toya's Father: ... Is Toya still asleep?
Toya's Mother: Toya...? He got up very early and took his breakfast into his room...
Toya's Father: He's having breakfast in his room? Where are his manners?
Toya's Mother: I understand how you feel... But he's been working very hard on this song of his lately. I'm actually a little worried.
Toya's Mother: I asked him if he'd like to sit and relax while having some breakfast with us, but he said he doesn't have time...
Toya: ... Good morning, Dad.
Toya's Father: Toya, don't tell me you haven't slept...
Toya: No, I did... I won't be able to perform very well if I don't...
Toya: Mom, do we have any bottles of mineral water left? I'd rather not waste time coming down for a drink each time.
Toya's Mother: Yes, we do... But are you sure about all this?
Toya: Yes. I apologize for making you worry so much...
Toya: But I have to do this... I have to...
Toya's Mother: Just don't push yourself too hard, okay...?
Toya: I'll be careful...
Toya's Mother: Is he really going to be okay...?
Toya's Father: ...
